<div style="background-color: #7700015C; border-left: 12px solid #D92121; padding: 2.5px 16.8px; margin: 0.5em 0em; font-size:36px; font-family:Orator STD;">General Description</div>
'''Level 464''' is an expansive yet finite steel mill stretching hundreds of thousands of kilometers in area. The level follows a 20th-century architectural design, featuring many industrial facets such as complex machinery, large piping, aeration systems, storage facilities, et cetera. The temperature averages around 39.5°C (103.1°F), creating a torrid climate hazardous for most wanderers. The factory's ceiling has skylights that reveal an unchanging overcast sky with no discernible celestial light source. A dry, hot atmosphere permeates the level. More elevated parts of the level, such as near the ceiling, are incredibly humid. This high humidity sometimes generates a faint high-laying fog, which can seldom drizzle.

'''Level 464'''<nowiki/>'s architectural layout and design are somewhat simple; the patterns may appear complicated initially due to the perplexing machine designs. As one starts to grasp the complexity of the level, the factory becomes easily navigable. Finding high ground assists wanderers in locating any vantage points, including safe areas or potential exits. Wanderers must exercise extreme caution when seeking high ground, as they could suffer third-degree burns if they touch the heated contraptions.

The machines present at '''Level 464''' are industrial-type contrivances made for manufacturing steel. Most of them are in operational condition. They emanate a loud noise, have rapidly moving parts, have a superheated metallic fluid running through them, and wanderers can operate the machines and tinker with them. If a machine is deactivated, the system it is part of deactivates like a kill switch, causing a chain reaction of malfunctions, sometimes even explosions. The machines are built with a regenerative material that reforms itself even after massive damage, sometimes generating new material during a reformation.

Ventilation systems in '''Level 464''' exert chilly, rapid winds spreading in various directions. The cold winds prevent areas in the level from overheating and usually increase in strength when temperatures rise in a specific area. The hot air emanating from the level's machinery clashing with the cold air from the ventilation systems can sometimes create weather patterns in '''Level 464''', sometimes catastrophically.

One may start having panic attacks, anxiety, and hallucinations under certain conditions in '''Level 464'''. These conditions include staying too close to a working machine for 3 minutes, prolonged isolation from other wanderers, or breathing the upper fog near the ceiling. These mental anomalies have no detrimental effects on wanderers unless they have lasting mental issues such as schizophrenia. Performing regular breathing exercises is enough to alleviate the mental effects. 

Throughout '''Level 464''', one may find small rooms filled with modern 2010s computer technology. Many computers are unable to boot up or are critically damaged. If one discovers a perfectly operable computer, one could use it for interlevel communication, running programs such as video games, or even controlling manufacturing systems, safely disabling them. A strange WiFi signal persists within the computer rooms, allowing wanderers to connect with others using their phones.

<div style="background-color: #7700015C; border-left: 12px solid #D92121; padding: 2.5px 16.8px; margin: 0.5em 0em; font-size:36px; font-family:Orator STD;">Entities</div>
{{Entity Class|no=N/A|Hab=Level 464|Agg=5|Int=1|Dan=5}}
{{Blurimage|caption=A photograph of a '''Cobble''', seconds after its ejection. |file=Midimage.jpg|hovertext=Ravaging Ropes, Searing Snakes|width=380px}}
'''The Cobble''' or simply '''Cobble,''' is an entity residing exclusively in '''Level 464'''. Its appearance takes on a large, slithering, scalding, molten steel cable. They usually dwell inside the level's complex machinery. They are aggressive towards wanderers and will attack on sense. When the entity is outside its residence machine, it no longer receives heat, which is essential to its health and is their main lifeblood. A '''Cobble''' dies when they solidify to inertness, usually 12 minutes without any heat source.

Any photographs taken of the '''Cobble''' have downgraded quality issues. They will often have noticeable resolution degradation and, in some rare cases, will be partially corrupted. The entity rarely disappears from photographs taken, but the low-quality image phenomenon will still influence the final image. The cause of this abnormality is unknown; some speculate it is due to a particle emitted from '''Cobble''' bodies that affects the camera.

'''Cobble''' will occasionally attack wanderers by violently ejecting themselves from their host machine. Once they eject, they travel at a rapid upward speed, sometimes reaching the level's ceiling. Their ejection trajectory is aimed at unpredictable directions but is attracted to to most biological lifeforms. '''Cobble''' can detect heat signatures and can discern lifeforms as they are the only sources of heat that move freely. Once they eject from their host machine, they will lose consciousness from about 45 seconds to a minute. 

After a '''Cobble''' gains consciousness, it will rapidly slither and sway its body towards wanderers. If there are no lifeforms in vicinity, the entity will remain motionless after it gains consciousness. The entity tends to halt its movement unpredictably for a few seconds between jitters. As the entity's temperature drops, its movement speed decreases, and jittering motions cease after five minutes. It is still hazardous to touch the entity until it dies since the heat may still deliver third-degree burns. 

The heat of a '''Cobble''' can reach a thousand degrees Celsius, and combined with the speed at which it moves, it can cut through wanderers. When it does, a surplus of adrenaline is generated, sustaining heat for ten minutes and then returning to its host machine. It will usually not look for other wanderers if it has already terminated one. The heat gained from the process is sent back into the host machine other nearby mechanisms, increasing emanations of noise and heat. The '''Cobble''' then spontaneously vanishes, ending its life, for other Cobbles to take its place.

'''Cobble''' are composed of a steel-like substance. It cannot switch states of matter, always remaining in a solid state despite surpassing their metal's melting point. They have varying lengths and widths, which constitutes their mass and capabilities. There are no remarkable body parts of a '''Cobble''', such as limbs, organs, and sensory systems, only appearing as a long noodle of molten steel.

The only other entities that reside on '''Level 464''' are [[Entity 44|'''Silver Slimes''']], a heat-resistant semi-sentient mold that thrives on the high iron content present on the many machines in the level. '''Silver Slimes''' are slow and only react towards wanderers that wander within their reach. These slimes are extremely deadly if they make contact with exposed skin, so exercising caution around these entities is highly suggested. 

<div style="background-color: #7700015C; border-left: 12px solid #D92121; padding: 2.5px 16.8px; margin: 0.5em 0em; font-size:36px; font-family:Orator STD;">Settlements</div>
===<span style="font-family:Orator STD;">Base Tau</span>===
The Major Explorer Group base Tau (τ) is the only known settlement in '''Level 464'''. It has an estimated population of 80. Established in late 2014, M.E.G. personnel use the base for research, guidance for wanderers, and trading. Only M.E.G. personnel are allowed to become a part of the colony.  The colony has no permanent population as the M.E.G. switches out staff once every month, with most workers having a 5-month shift. They have no sustainable food or water source, receiving sustenance from weekly outside shipments. Their main goals in '''Level 464''' are to understand more about it and its level-exclusive entity, reverse engineer the level's technology, and create a safe environment for themselves to live in.

